-- European Stocks Extend Losses as U.S. Consumer Sentiment Misses Forecasts
-- Andrew Rummer
-- 2010-07-16T14:00:08Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-16/european-stocks-extend-losses-as-u-s-consumer-sentiment-misses-forecasts.html

          
          
             European stocks extended their
decline as the Thomson Reuters/University of Michigan
preliminary index of U.S. consumer sentiment fell more than
forecast.  
 The Stoxx Europe 600 Index slid 1.7 percent to 248.61 at
2:58 p.m. in London, having earlier risen as much as 0.5
percent.  
          
          


  


        